metadata.name: Pedro Navaja
metadata.description:
This is the story of ‘Pedro Navaja’: a dangerous man in the streets of New York, on the prowl for a victim.  A story first told in 1978 by Ruben Blades and Willie Colon in their classic Salsa hit of the same name.

Although the lyrics tell a dark story, the song sparks beautiful memories for me.

It’s the love of salsa I inherited from my dad,  
It’s dancing in bars in Puerto Rico,  
It’s the joy in the faces of everyone around,  
It’s love for Latin America and its rich history,  
It’s my love for Puerto Rico.
